{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-6677c777ce65", "date": "2026-07-21", "stream": "news", "headline": "Sinaloa cartel co-founder 'El Mayo' sentenced to life, ordered to forfeit $15 billion", "summary": "A US federal judge in Brooklyn sentenced Ismael 'El Mayo' Zambada Garcia to life without parole and ordered him to forfeit $15 billion in drug profits.", "url": "https://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/co-founder-sinaloa-cartel-ismael-el-mayo-zambada-garcia-sentenced-life-prison-and-ordered", "source_domain": "justice.gov", "tier": "T1", "tags": ["new source"], "topics": ["world"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "The Justice Department said Zambada, 76, was sentenced in Brooklyn by Judge Brian M. Cogan; he had pleaded guilty in August 2025 to running a continuing criminal enterprise and to racketeering, capping a decades-long career that ended with his arrest in July 2024. The $15 billion forfeiture, a court order to surrender criminal proceeds, is among the largest ever in a US drug case.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-21-news-sinaloa-cartel-co-founder-el-mayo-sentenced-to-l", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-21", "event_date": "2026-07-20", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Ismael Zambada", "Sinaloa Cartel", "US Department of Justice"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "updated": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-21-news-sinaloa-cartel-co-founder-el-mayo-sentenced-to-l"], "editions": ["2026-07-21-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-6677c777ce65", "edition": "2026-07-21-news", "fields": {"display_body": "The Justice Department said Zambada, 76, was sentenced in Brooklyn by Judge Brian M. Cogan; he had pleaded guilty in August 2025 to running a continuing criminal enterprise and to racketeering, capping a decades-long career that ended with his arrest in July 2024. The $15 billion forfeiture, a court order to surrender criminal proceeds, is among the largest ever in a US drug case.", "why": "", "importance": 1, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-9f3a50809124", "date": "2026-07-21", "stream": "news", "headline": "France's parliament set to vote on barring under-15s from social media", "summary": "France's parliament was scheduled to vote Tuesday on a Macron-backed bill barring under-15s from social media, a European first; if adopted it takes effect in September with age-verification requirements.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/monde/la-france-sapprete-a-interdire-les-reseaux-sociaux-aux-moins-de-15-ans-une-premiere-en-europe", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["politics", "tech"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "With the Senate voting in the afternoon and the National Assembly in the evening, the law, if adopted as expected, would take effect in September and require platforms to verify users' ages; no penalties are foreseen for families. As of this brief the vote had not yet been held, so the outcome is not final.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-21-news-france-s-parliament-set-to-vote-on-barring-under", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-21", "event_date": "2026-07-21", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["France", "Emmanuel Macron"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "updated": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-21-news-france-s-parliament-set-to-vote-on-barring-under"], "editions": ["2026-07-21-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-9f3a50809124", "edition": "2026-07-21-news", "fields": {"display_body": "With the Senate voting in the afternoon and the National Assembly in the evening, the law, if adopted as expected, would take effect in September and require platforms to verify users' ages; no penalties are foreseen for families. As of this brief the vote had not yet been held, so the outcome is not final.", "why": "", "importance": 1, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-f18f27a7737f", "date": "2026-07-21", "stream": "news", "headline": "Swatch Group reports first-half sales up 8.5% at constant currency", "summary": "Swatch Group said first-half sales rose 8.5% at constant exchange rates to 3.12 billion francs and that it is regaining market share, though profitability remains under pressure.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/economie/swatch-group-accelere-sa-croissance-et-vise-un-rebond-de-sa-rentabilite", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["economy", "switzerland"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "At current exchange rates the gain narrowed to 2%, dragged by a negative currency effect of nearly 200 million francs; the Biel-based group led by Nick Hayek pointed to a strong spring acceleration while acknowledging that profitability remains under pressure.", "why": "Swatch is a bellwether for the Swiss watch industry, and a rebound after a weak stretch signals firmer demand, though the currency drag underscores how the strong franc keeps eating into exporters' results.", "thread_id": "2026-07-21-news-swatch-group-reports-first-half-sales-up-8-5-at", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-21", "event_date": "2026-07-21", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Swatch Group", "Nick Hayek"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "updated": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-21-news-swatch-group-reports-first-half-sales-up-8-5-at"], "editions": ["2026-07-21-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-f18f27a7737f", "edition": "2026-07-21-news", "fields": {"display_body": "At current exchange rates the gain narrowed to 2%, dragged by a negative currency effect of nearly 200 million francs; the Biel-based group led by Nick Hayek pointed to a strong spring acceleration while acknowledging that profitability remains under pressure.", "why": "Swatch is a bellwether for the Swiss watch industry, and a rebound after a weak stretch signals firmer demand, though the currency drag underscores how the strong franc keeps eating into exporters' results.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
{"ev": "seen", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "story": {"id": "st-26579d2ec62b", "date": "2026-07-21", "stream": "news", "headline": "Stadler Rail refuses to pay 10-million-franc ransom after cyberattack", "summary": "Swiss trainmaker Stadler Rail said it will not pay a 10-million-franc ransom after the Everest group stole technical data from a supplier in mid-July; its own systems were not compromised.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/economie/victime-dune-cyberattaque-stadler-rail-refuse-de-payer-une-rancon-de-10-millions-de-francs", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland", "economy"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The Thurgau-based company said its own IT systems were not compromised and production continues normally; it has filed a criminal complaint.", "why": "A visible refusal to pay by a flagship Swiss industrial firm sets a notable example on ransom demands, even as the theft of supplier data shows the exposure runs through the wider supply chain, not just a company's own network.", "thread_id": "2026-07-21-news-stadler-rail-refuses-to-pay-10-million-franc-ran", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-21", "event_date": "2026-07-21", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": "", "entities": ["Stadler Rail", "Everest"], "status": "settled", "first_seen": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "updated": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "legacy_ids": ["2026-07-21-news-stadler-rail-refuses-to-pay-10-million-franc-ran"], "editions": ["2026-07-21-news"], "origin": "writer:news", "streams": ["news"]}}
{"ev": "publish", "ts": "2026-07-21T10:11:57Z", "actor": "news", "id": "st-26579d2ec62b", "edition": "2026-07-21-news", "fields": {"display_body": "The Thurgau-based company said its own IT systems were not compromised and production continues normally; it has filed a criminal complaint.", "why": "A visible refusal to pay by a flagship Swiss industrial firm sets a notable example on ransom demands, even as the theft of supplier data shows the exposure runs through the wider supply chain, not just a company's own network.", "importance": 2, "status": "settled"}}
